President Joe Biden and Chancellor Angela Merkel held a discussion on the situation in Afghanistan. They commended the joint efforts of their military and civilian personnel in Kabul to evacuate their citizens, vulnerable Afghans, and Afghan nationals who contributed to security and development in the country over the past two decades. The leaders also emphasized the importance of coordinating humanitarian aid for vulnerable Afghans and supporting neighboring states. They agreed to further plan this work in an upcoming virtual meeting of G7 partners.